data.text:
Clint Dempsey Sidelined Over Irregular Heartbeat

Clint Dempsey's club Seattle Sounders confirmed that the 33-year-old footballer would be sidelined from this weekend's Major League Soccer clash with the Portland Timbers in Oregon

Copa America: Clint Dempsey Helps USA Enter Quarter-Final, Paraguay Eliminated

Clint Dempsey scored for the United States as they defeated Paraguay to enter the quarter-finals of the 2016 Copa America

Copa America: Clint Dempsey Helps United States Thrash Costa Rica 4-0

Clint Dempsey scored his 50th international goal as United States bounced back from their 2-0 loss to Colombia in the opening game to trounce Costa Rica 4-0 in the 2016 Copa America.

Seattle Sounders Star Clint Dempsey Banned For Three Games for Referee Incident

Clint Dempsey will miss the next three Seattle Sounders matches in Major League Soccer. Dempsey tore up the referee's notepad in a 3-1 loss to Portland in the US Open Cup.

FIFA World Cup, United States vs Portugal: Silvestre Varela's Late Header Keeps Portugal in Hunt for Pre-Quarters

Silvestre Varela netted in the final minute of stoppage time as Portugal secured a 2-2 draw with the United States to earn one crucial point.

Clint Dempsey returns to struggling Fulham on two-month loan

The 30-year-old, who plays for the Seattle Sounders in the MLS, spent five and a half seasons at Craven Cottage in his first spell after signing in January 2007 from New England Revolution.

Clint Dempsey to return to Fulham on loan

Dempsey scored 50 goals in 184 league matches for Fulham from 2007-12. He left for Tottenham before moving to the Seattle Sounders in August.
